<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1297246" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/trail.jpg?resize=500%2C623&#038;ssl=1" alt="LASG shuts Costain  road for rail project" width="500" height="623" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/trail.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/trail.jpg?resize=241%2C300&amp;ssl=1 241w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/trail.jpg?resize=47%2C58&amp;ssl=1 47w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/trail.jpg?resize=156%2C194&amp;ssl=1 156w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/trail.jpg?resize=104%2C130&amp;ssl=1 104w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/trail.jpg?resize=560%2C697&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Lagos State Government has appealed to motoring public to cooperate with traffic officials as Toyin Level Crossing around Okusanya Street Costain area will subsequently be closed down on the 21st and 22nd of January, 2020 from 6:00pm to 12:00pm in the ongoing construction of rail way project. The state Commissioner for Transportation, DT. Frederic Oladeinde, in a statement, Friday said, “In line with the Nigerian Railway Modernization Project (Lagos-Ibadan section) with extension to Lagos Port at Apapa, the Lagos State Government will be hoisting beams for the new Costain Bridge from Saturday 18th to Sunday 19th January, 2020. “As a result, Toyin Level Crossing around Okusanya Street will subsequently be closed down on the 21st and 22nd of January, 2020.” He said alternative routes have been provided for road users to utilize during the course of the construction to ensure motorists reach their various destinations with ease. Oladeinde said motorists plying costain axis will be diverted to the newly completed section of the new bridge, while those driving along Okusanya Street are advised to make use of Jonathan Coker Street to get to their destinations. “The closure has been slated at this time, to ensure there is smooth and uninterrupted flow of work on the rail tracks. “Lagos State Government is hereby appealing to residents of the state, especially motorists that ply these corridors to bear the pains, as the project is aimed at achieving a seamless multi modal transport system that will meet the transportation need of a larger population,” Oladeinde pleaded. Vanguard The Lagos State Government ( LASG) on Wednesday announced that it would close two roads to traffic on Jan.9 and Jan.11 respectively. It said that this was to facilitate the completion of the construction of the ongoing Lagos -Ibadan standard guage rail line within where the roads were located. The… January 9, 2020 In "News" The Lagos State Government (LASG) on Tuesday said  that it would be closing  the Adejobi axis of the Agege Motor Road to facilitate the quick completion of the ongoing construction of the Lagos-Ibadan standard guage rail line. The Public Affairs unit of the Ministry of Transportation said in a statement… December 31, 2019 In "News" THE Lagos State Government yesterday said it was looking at other possible options, other than the bringing down the Jibowu and Costain overhead bridges in order to accommodate the $1.5bn Lagos-Ibadan standard gauge rail project. November 8, 2017 In "News"